-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Mon Aug 04, 2014 06:35AM EDT
-- None



Aug 4 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1030 GMT on Monday:

** Australia's Treasury Wine Estates Ltd <TWE.AX> is opening its books to Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co LP <KKR.N> after the private equity giant hiked its takeover offer to $3.15 billion, raising the prospect of a bidding war for the world's No.2 winemaker. [ID:nL4N0Q90PJ]  ** Oman National Investment Corp Holding <ONIC.OM> said it would discuss a possible merger with Oman International Development and Investment Co <OMAN.OM> at its next board meeting. [ID:nL6N0QA0X7]  ** German airport operator Fraport AG <FRAG.DE> has bought a U.S.-based manager of retail space at four U.S. airports as it looks to expand its profitable retail operations and gain a foothold in the United States. [ID:nL6N0QA1L3]  ** U.S. software firm Hyland Co raised its bid for peer ReadSoft AB <RSOFb.ST> for a second time, valuing the Swedish firm at 1.69 billion Swedish crowns ($245.5 million) and heating up a bidding war with U.S. printer maker Lexmark International Inc <LXK.N>. [ID:nL6N0QA1H6]  ** The Co-operative Group <42TE.L> said it had agreed to sell its farm business to charitable body the Wellcome Trust for 249 million pounds ($418.7 million). [ID:nFWN0Q9001]  ** Billionaire Li Ka-shing's Cheung Kong Holdings Ltd <0001.HK> is considering a bid for aircraft being sold by private equity firm Terra Firma-owned lessor AWAS Aviation Capital Ltd, a deal which sources said could be worth about $5 billion. [ID:nL4N0QA0B6]  ** Spanish bank Popular <POP.MC> said it had agreed to a preliminary deal to sell 51 percent of its stake in its credit card business to U.S. investment management firm Varde Partners Inc. [ID:nL6N0QA1CN]  ** Shares in Australia's Horizon Oil Ltd <HZN.AX> slumped  after its merger with Roc Oil Co Ltd <ROC.AX> was trumped by Chinese conglomerate Fosun International Ltd <0656.HK>, which offered 69 Australian cents per share, a 10 percent premium to Roc's close last Friday. [ID:nS9N0P801A]  ** Boutique investment bank Evercore Partners Inc <EVR.N> said on Sunday that it planned to buy the operating business of ISI International Strategy & Investment, an independent research-driven equity sales and agency trading firm. [ID:nASB08M1H]